# Windsurf rules — context-router

This repo dogfoods its own tool. Windsurf sessions working here MUST follow the bootstrap contract:

**→ Read `.handover/prompts/agent-bootstrap.md` before doing anything else.**

That file is the single source of truth for required start/end-of-session calls, how to keep the index live, when to record architectural decisions, and repo conventions.

For repo-specific quality rules, also read `CLAUDE.md`.

---

**Windsurf MCP setup** — `.windsurf/mcp_config.json`:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "context-router": {
      "command": "context-router mcp",
      "transport": "stdio"
    }
  }
}
```

Quick rules:

- Before opening any file, call `search_memory(query="<task>")` and `get_context_pack(mode="handover")`.
- Run `context-router watch` in a terminal to keep the index live.
- After every completed task, call `save_observation(...)` and commit `.context-router/memory/observations/`.
- One conventional-commit per logical concern. Tests green before push (`uv run pytest`).

No other knowledge-graph tools are wired into this repo. Do not introduce `code-review-graph`, `aider-repomap`, or similar — context-router is the local stack.
